
Overview of noun loft

The noun loft has 4 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                           
1. (1) loft -- (floor consisting of a large unpartitioned space over a factory or warehouse or other commercial space)
2. (1) loft, attic, garret -- (floor consisting of open space at the top of a house just below roof; often used for storage)
3. loft -- ((golf) the backward slant on the head of some golf clubs that is designed to drive the ball high in the air)
4. loft, pigeon loft -- (a raised shelter in which pigeons are kept)

Overview of verb loft

The verb loft has 4 senses (no senses from tagged texts)
                                         
1. loft -- (store in a loft)
2. loft -- (propel through the air; "The rocket lofted the space shuttle into the air")
3. loft -- (kick or strike high in the air; "loft a ball")
4. loft -- (lay out a full-scale working drawing of the lines of a vessel's hull)
